What is a Scaffold?
Simple definition: A Scaffold is the main structure of your app screen. It provides the basic Material Design layout with an AppBar, body, floating buttons, drawers, and more.

Think of it like: The frame of a house - it holds everything together and provides the structure.

Why Do You Need Scaffold?
Without a Scaffold, your screen would be empty. The Scaffold gives you:

Feature	                     What It Provides
appBar	                     The top bar with title and actions
body	                       The main content of your screen
floatingActionButton	       A floating button (like +)
bottomNavigationBar	         Bottom tabs
drawer	                     Side menu that slides in
bottomSheet	                 Panel that slides up from bottom
backgroundColor	             Screen background color



The 7 Main Properties=======================================================================================


1️⃣ appBar (Top Bar)
What it does: The bar at the top of the screen.

dart
Scaffold(
  appBar: AppBar(
    title: Text('My App'),
    backgroundColor: Colors.blue,
  ),
  body: ...,
)



2️⃣ body (Main Content)
What it does: The main content of your screen (fills the space below the AppBar).

dart
Scaffold(
  appBar: AppBar(title: Text('My App')),
  body: Center(
    child: Text('Hello World'),
  ),
)



3️⃣ floatingActionButton (FAB)
What it does: A circular button that "floats" above the content (usually for primary actions).

dart
Scaffold(
  appBar: AppBar(title: Text('My App')),
  body: Center(child: Text('Hello')),
  floatingActionButton: FloatingActionButton(
    onPressed: () {
      print('FAB clicked!');
    },
    child: Icon(Icons.add),
  ),
)



4️⃣ bottomNavigationBar (Bottom Tabs)
What it does: A bar at the bottom with tabs for navigation.

dart
Scaffold(
  appBar: AppBar(title: Text('My App')),
  body: Center(child: Text('Home')),
  bottomNavigationBar: BottomNavigationBar(
    items: [
      BottomNavigationBarItem(icon: Icon(Icons.home), label: 'Home'),
      BottomNavigationBarItem(icon: Icon(Icons.settings), label: 'Settings'),
    ],
  ),
)




5️⃣ drawer (Side Menu)
What it does: A menu that slides in from the left side.

dart
Scaffold(
  appBar: AppBar(title: Text('My App')),
  body: Center(child: Text('Hello')),
  drawer: Drawer(
    child: ListView(
      children: [
        DrawerHeader(child: Text('Menu')),
        ListTile(title: Text('Home')),
        ListTile(title: Text('Settings')),
      ],
    ),
  ),
)




6️⃣ backgroundColor (Background Color)
What it does: Sets the background color of the Scaffold.

dart
Scaffold(
  backgroundColor: Colors.blueGrey[50],
  appBar: AppBar(title: Text('My App')),
  body: Center(child: Text('Hello')),
)



7️⃣ resizeToAvoidBottomInset (Keyboard Handling)
What it does: Controls whether the body resizes when the keyboard appears.

dart
Scaffold(
  resizeToAvoidBottomInset: false,  // Keyboard won't resize body
  appBar: AppBar(title: Text('My App')),
  body: Center(child: TextField()),
)

Default: true (body resizes to make room for keyboard)





